cs.CL, cs.HC, cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG

This paper focuses on evaluating the usability of automatically generated captions for people who are Deaf or Hard of Hearing, which falls under the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the development of a new evaluation metric, which could fall under the categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves a user study, which could also fall under the category of sound (cs.SD) as it pertains to the evaluation of speech recognition technology.
